captions.text: -Hey, everyone.

I'm Mindy with Cute
Girls Hairstyles,

and today, I'm here
with Miss Bailey.
-Hello, guys.

-And she and i are
going to show you

how to do a hairstyle we're
calling laced fishtail.

Now, I saw this
picture on Instagram.
I loved it.

I knew I needed to teach you
guys a tutorial because to me

this is like a perfect
hairstyle for summer,
like it screams summer.

It's loose and
girlie and romantic,

but it's pulled
out of your face.

So to me-- I don't know--
it have that really beach,

swimming pool vibe, which is
really great for summertime.

OK, so to begin with,
on Bailey's hair,
I gave her a side part.

I did one part right down the
middle of her head on this one.

And I'm going to start with
the heavy side over her hair

although it doesn't really
particularly matter.

I'm going to pick
up a little section,

and I'm going to divide
it into three strands.

And we're going to
be lace braiding.

I'm going to be doing a
regular French braid, not
a Dutch version.

But the only difference
is on a lace braid,

sometimes you pick up from
the top and add hair in.

This time, I'm going to be
picking up hair from the bottom
and adding it in.

So on this top
strand, I'm just going

to continue to work
it through the braid.

When I get to this bottom
piece-- do a little bit more--

I'm going to take a
little piece of hair

and add it into that section
and continue the braid.

So no adding in hair
at the top, continue
to add hair in on the bottom.

And I'm going to keep this
a good, probably, 2 to 2
and 1/2 inches above her ear.

I don't want it to go super
close down on her ear.

I want it to be more like
a-- I don't know-- a crown

effect on the top of
your head and less

like pulled back
around her ears.

So I'm going to keep going and
adding in hair from the bottom.

And I'm just trying to take
smaller sections so that we

get a little more lace braiding
as we go along the back.

You don't want it too
chunky on the sides.

And when I get to about the
ear, maybe just slightly

behind the ear--
I'll do one more--

I'm going to stop
adding in hair.

And I'm just going to continue
the braid at this point

because that's as much hair
as I want to use right now.

And Bailey has layers,
which is not problem,

we're just going
to make those work.

And don't worry about it if
you have some poking out,
we'll work them in later.

So you can see I'm
just continuing

the braid a little
bit because its just

going to make it a
little easier to hang
on to while I do the other side.

Now, Miss Bailey, will
you hold that for me.
There you go.

Now, I'm going to go
on the other side--

flip her around-- and
do the same thing.

This is the non-heavy
side of the braid,

so this one's going to
be a little less thick--
and continue same pattern.

Now, I'm going to
swing her back around.

When you get done with
your two side braids,

the lace braids,
then you're going

to take them and cross
them in the back.

Bailey has a little bit of
fringe from her bangs popping

out just right here, so I'm
going to just tuck those under,

and I'm going to cross that
as the under piece, and then

anything else that still
pops out when we're done,
we'll just bobby pin.

I'm going to try to hold
those as tight as possible
against her head.

I'm going to pick up a
little bit hair on this side,

and I'm going to cross
it all the way over

and add it in to that
piece on the left.

Now, I'm going to take
some hair from the left,

a little section,
cross it over that

strand we were holding
before, and into the section
on the right.

So you still are only
dealing with two sections.

You're just adding hair,
crossing it over each other.

So again, I'm going to
take some from the right,

cross it up and over
completely, and add it
in to the piece on the left.

And make sure that I have
enough looseness on the top.
That looks good.
And then just keep going.

Now, I'm not doing like super
tiny sections or anything
like that.

I'm actually trying to
do a little bit bigger

stranding than I normally
would for a fishtail

because I want to give the
illusion that you're not sure

whether this is actually a
French braid or fishtail braid.

That's what I am heading for, so
we're just going to keep going

and keep switching the hair up
and over until all of that hair

that was underneath
before is now

added into one of
the two sections.
We're just about there.

So now, we still have, you can
see, just our two sections.

And now, we're going to go just
right into a normal fishtail,

which means we're going to
take hair from one side, one

outside edge of the
fishtail, and cross it
right over the top.
I don't like that one.
There we go.

And add it into the
piece on the other side,

and do the same
thing on this side.

OK, when you're done with
at the end of your fishtail,

you're just going to
get an elastic-- Or
not, that one went crazy.

Get out another
elastic and secure it.

And then I'm going to
go back and just pull

a little bit try to soften this
up just a little, not too much.
There, that looks really good.

And there you have your
lace braid fishtail.
Fantastic!
OK, let's do the final spin.
I'm loving this one.

I think, legitimately,
that one would

be perfect for straight out
of the beach or the ocean

on the beach or out of
the pool because it really

would work fantastic,
even on wet hair.

So there you go, I just gave
you the best summer hairdo.

-And if you guys really
want to see a funny video,

go check out the video
that Brooklyn and I put up
on our channel, the last one.

It's called Not My
Arms Makeup Challenge

where Brooklyn does
my makeup, basically,

blindly while she's
sitting behind me.
It's really funny.

She gave me a bloody
nose and everything.
-And you'll just have watch it.
It's over--

-You should definitely
go check it out.

--on Brooklyn and
Bailey's channel,

which is called
Brooklyn and Bailey,

and you can find it in
the description box below.
Or, we'll put a link up here.
You can check it out.
It's really funny.

Actually, one of
my favorite videos.

Listen, you can hear
it on the video.
I'm behind the camera laughing.
-Giggling.

-Like trying so
hard not to because

I didn't want to be like
noisy behind the mic.
-It was so funny.

-But every once
and a while, you'll

hear me giggle because it
was really just that funny,

and Kamri and I just
couldn't help it.

We were just laughing
as they were doing it.
-It was funny.
-It was great.
Go check it out.
We'll see you guys next Sunday.
Toodles!
-Bye!
I
-I love you very much!
